I Kissed Dating Goodbye is a best-selling[citation needed] 1997 book by Joshua Harris. The book focuses on Harris' disenchantment with the contemporary secular dating scene, and offers ideas for improvement, alternative dating/courting practices, and a view that singleness need not be a burden nor characterized by what Harris describes as "selfishness."As of February 2006, the book had sold over a million copies since its 1997 printing.[citation needed]